    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="1382"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1382">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/217.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Willard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 10, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your April 8. You may inform the Spanish Government that this Government is doing
                    everything within the scope of its powers for the protection of Spanish subjects
                    and their properties in Mexico. A telegram from the Consular Agent at Juarez
                    states that General Carranza has given out statement to the effect that property
                    of Spaniards expelled from Torreon will not be confiscated.</p>
                <p>Everything possible is being done to induce Carranza to revoke the order of
                    expulsion. Hereafter you will be kept fully informed by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
